  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottoms from going soggy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to a bowl with your <strong>dried sage</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Divide the mixture into 6 per person and roll into small meatballs</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303961514-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303961514-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303961514-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303961514-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303961514-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>tomato paste</strong> with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303967634-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303967634-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303967634-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303967634-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303967634-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>spinach </strong>to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under the cold tap until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze the water out of the spinach as much as you can</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606303978520-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606303978520-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606303978520-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606303978520-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606303978520-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Spread the <strong>tomato sauce </strong>on your <strong>pizza base[s]</strong> evenly with the back of a spoon</p><p>Top with the<strong> torn mozzarella</strong>, piles of <strong>wilted spinach</strong> and the<strong> pork & sage stuffing balls</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606303990294-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606303990294-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606303990294-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606303990294-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606303990294-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until the cheese has melted, the base is crisp and the pork & sage stuffing balls are cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>pork & sage stuffing pizza[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1606304001243-x200.jpg",
